    <h1>Philips Hue Play gra&#xAD;di&#xAD;ent light&#xAD;strip</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200909/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-09"><time>2020-09-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TECH</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Lo­cal avail­abil­ity and pric­ing to be an­nounced</p>
    <p>Fans of Philips’ Am­bi­light tele­vi­sions can now add their mood-chang­ing LEDs to any TV set.</p>
    <p>The newly an­nounced Philips Hue Play gra­di­ent light­strip sticks to the back of a TV set and syn­chro­nises its LEDs with the on-screen con­tent.</p>
    <p>You will need a separately sold Hue Bridge.</p>
    <p>The light­strip’s LEDs of­fer more than 16 mil­lion colours. It comes in three sizes, for 55-, 65- and 75-inch TV sets.</p>
    <p>To cus­tomise the LEDs’ colours, speed and in­ten­sity, users will need the Hue Sync desk­top app or the Hue Play HDMI sync box with the Hue Sync mo­bile app.</p>

